>Mr Lilley:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> I want to move on to another—</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Lord Deben</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">If I may say so, w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e did not establish that I could not envisage</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. We established that I could envisage the evidence. What I could not do was to tell you in advance what that evidence might be. I could</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> say that there are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> a range of things that could turn out to be true that would change my view</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. B</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ut it is incorrect to say that I suggested that I could not envisage such a circumstance</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> because of course I can and anybody who said that they could not is not treating science seriously</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Dr Kennedy:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">It is important to say, as well, that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-siz